post_text:
Upcoming Seniors, please note; before you register for any SAT/ACT tests this year, you should consider this message. As always, please reach out to any colleges you are interested in to verify their SAT/ACT testing requirements.
-Mrs. Rosales

Message from The State University of NY (SUNY)
"We are writing to announce SUNY's decision to temporarily suspend SAT/ACT testing requirements for rising high school seniors intending to enroll at a SUNY bachelor‚Äôs degree-granting campus for the 2021-2022 academic year. This temporary change of admission eligibility requirements applies to the spring 2021, fall 2021, and spring 2022 cycles only.

SUNY will maintain its longstanding commitment to holistic review of student applicants that includes grades, program of study, exam scores, academic achievements, non-academic achievements, and other activities that allow for the evaluation of the potential success of a candidate for admission.

We trust that this temporary change in testing requirements will remove a potential barrier for students during these uncertain times."

A message for our recent graduates:
The 2020-21 New York State Excelsior Scholarship application has been released and will remain open until August 31, 2020. For your reference, please note that the NYS Higher Education Services Corporation (HESC) has advised the following:

"The COVID-19 pandemic has dramatically reduced state revenues and the processing of new applications is pending on Federal assistance, which has been delayed since April. Excelsior Scholarship awards may have to be reduced and/or prioritized for current recipients as provided for under the program."

We continue to encourage students to submit the application and remain hopeful with regard to funding.

Thank you for your assistance,
Recruitment Response Center
The State University of New York
1.800.342.3811 or 518.320.1888

post_text:
July 16, 2020

I wanted to communicate a few updates. We had our first reopening committee meeting today made up staff, parents and a student. Yesterday, we sent out a survey to all families via email. I have placed this survey on our homepage and I will include it again in an email for you to provide us your feedback https://forms.gle/jG4oJcyeThP4GRM18 I provided the committee with the guidance documents we have received to date. We are awaiting a lengthy and more specific document from the New York State Education Department on reopening.

Next, I wanted to let you know that the New York State Public High School Athletic Association has delayed the start of fall sports and has cancelled the fall championships.

Please know that your leadership team and committee are committed to working together as a team to ensure the safe return of our students and staff. If you have any questions, please feel free to reach out to your principal. I am also more than willing to talk at any time.

Thank you for your support.

Ned Dale
Superintendent
ndale@elbacsd.org
585-757-9967 Ext 1034

post_text:
June 25, 2020

As you may be aware, New York State is now allowing outdoor graduations with a maximum attendance of 150 people. We planned graduation for Saturday, June 27, 2020 at 10:00 a.m. Today, we contacted all of the families from the Class of 2020, as well as the individuals that will be supporting our program. Based on the feedback and pending weather forecast for Saturday, we wanted to let everyone know the Class of 2020 graduation will now be on Friday, June 26, 2020 at 6:30 p.m. in the front of the school. Graduates will be provided 6 tickets each for their invited guests during rehearsal on Friday at 10:00.

There is limited handicap parking in the front bus loop, as well as in the north lot. Graduates are being asked to park in the back parking lot near the elementary entrance and enter the back auditorium entrance for lining up.

We look forward to seeing everyone tomorrow night!

Sincerely,
Ned Dale
Superintendent

Just a reminder for those returning ballots - Please fill out the front with your date, name, and address to verify who is voting. Also, you must sign the statement on the back of the return envelope for your ballot to be counted. Without a signed statement we cannot count it.

For those worried about putting their names on ballots. To ensure confidentiality of voting - the District will follow these procedures: Ballots will not opened until 5:01 pm on June 9th. Ballots will be opened and will remain folded and placed back in the ballot box. Once all the ballots are in the ballot box and mixed - they will then be taken out and counting will begin.
Please call Donna Harris, District Clerk at 757-9967 x1033 if you have any questions. Thank you!

post_text:
Good Afternoon.

In an effort to keep our students' food safe, we will be changing our food delivery dates and pick up window starting this Thursday due to the rising summer temperatures. We will no longer be serving on Mondays. Students will be getting three breakfasts and lunches on Thursdays and two on Tuesdays. If you are picking meals up, we will be at the north door from 10:00-11:00 a.m. on Tuesdays and Thursdays only. If meals are being delivered on Tuesdays and Thursdays, we are asking that a cooler be placed outside your door to keep the food cold. Our goal is to make sure that all meals do not pose a risk to our students during the summer temperatures.

Stay safe!
Ned Dale
Superintendent

post_text:
Good Afternoon. Teachers will be packing up UPK-6 belongings and have them in the Sherwood gym to retrieve this week. Students with personal belongings in classrooms for grades 7-12 will find them on a desk outside of their classrooms. Textbooks and library books that are not being used need to be returned to the classroom or library. Lockers will be open for everyone to access as well. Retrieval times for students with the last name A-J is Wednesday, May 6 from 3-6 p.m. and for families with the last name K-Z will be Thursday, May 7, 3-6 p.m. Please plan on entering at the North door or Bus loop entrance only. We will be monitoring the number of people in the building at one time.

Thank you.

Ned Dale

Superintendent

post_text:
Dear Elba Families,
Many communities have been participating in the ‚ÄúAdopt A Senior‚Äù activity; this allows community members the opportunity to celebrate a graduating senior who might be sad over missing their typical senior year celebrations. It is a way to lift their spirits! This might look like a small care package of their favorite snacks, a special t-shirt, or a fun sign. The possibilities are endless!

We would like to determine if there is interest in our Lancer community. Please email HS principal Gretchen Rosales at grosales@elbacsd.org or HS counselor Alison Riner at ariner@elbacsd.org if you are interested in ‚Äúadopting‚Äù a senior. Once we have a list, we will coordinate with those interested.

#OneElba

Dear AP Students and Parents:

AP Exam Demo (available May 4): AP students should use the clickable exam demo to practice the different ways to submit their exam responses. The demo will help students confirm that their testing device will be able to access and run the online exam. If they can‚Äôt access the demo, the final slide of the Testing Guide can help them troubleshoot. The sample content in the demo will be the same for all users and isn't a practice exam. *** The College Board will send educators and students an email to remind them when the demo is available.*** Please encourage your students to take this important preparation step.

Students: please read the important letter regarding the AP exams that came with your report card last week.

post_text:
April 21, 2020

I wanted to let everyone know that Elba High School was recognized by U.S. News & World Report as one of the "Best High Schools" for 2020. This honor and recognition is a positive reflection of the leadership and hard work by all of our K-12 staff to ensure our students are inspired and empowered to be continuous learners! It further supports one of our goals to improve academic programs, as we strive to meet our mission! We want to thank our parents and community, as we know it takes a village to raise our children!

Go Lancers!
Ned Dale
Superintendent

post_text: Elba Lancer family: If you are interested in helping out, here is a community service project coordinated by Mrs. Williams! Bring any fabric scraps to the lunch pick-up on Monday, Tuesday, and Thursday and a sewing brigade will make them into face masks. Any type of fabric cut into 6x9 inch squares will be accepted (think t-shirts, flannels, sheets, etc). Questions? Please email Mrs. Williams at lwilliams@elbacsd.org (there will be a box available during this time - just toss your fabric into it). Thank you for helping this worthwhile cause!

post_text:
Students in 9th and 10th grade are working on a combined, interdisciplinary project with their teachers on the global efforts that took place during World War II and comparing them to the global efforts that are taking place now during the current pandemic. Connecting the past to today is a critical part of learning.

Kudos to Mr. DeMare, Mrs. Ellingham, Mrs. Kent, Mr. Lembo, Mrs. Soller, and Mrs. Williams for coming up with a timely and creative project for our students!

post_text:
The Elba school community is joining the Batavia community and the Oakfield community (and probably many others) in going on a "bear hunt!" If you happen to have a teddy bear laying around, place it in your window. Then, when families need to get out of the house, they can go on a bear hunt, looking for the teddy bears in windows. One of our pre-k students has counted 46 bears already! How many will you count?

If you'd like, feel free to make it a reading activity too! Just click the link below to see an animated read aloud of the book "We're going on a bear hunt"!

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Waoa3iG3bZ4

Good Afternoon.

We wanted to let everyone know that we will be distributing chromebooks for students in Kindergarten through Grade 6 on Wednesday from 7 a.m. through 12:00 noon. For students in grades 7-12 that didn't retrieve their chromebook last week, please email or call Mrs. Rosales. We will retrieve your chromebook and have it ready for you to pick up on Wednesday between 7:00-12:00 noon. Individuals that had requested printed packets, please plan on picking these up on Wednesday as well with your device in the front bus loop. Materials not picked up by noon will be mailed as previously communicated.

A full update from Elba will be coming out later today. Once again, we thank you for your support.

Ned Dale
Superintendent
Elba Central School District
57 S. Main Street PO Box 370
Elba, New York 14058
(585)757-9967 Ext. 1034

post_text:
March 19, 2020

I wanted to communicate a change for all of our students and families with regard to our meal distribution program. Starting Monday, we will be serving Monday through Friday. All families are welcome to come to school for a ‚Äúgrab and go‚Äù breakfast and lunch every day next week. We are also continuing to deliver as well. There is no cost to families. Please come to the North entrance during the hours of 10:00 in the morning until 12:00. Students will get their breakfast and lunch daily.

We have finished a deep clean of the building. Only essential staff will be on campus for specific reasons. We have made every accommodation for individuals to work from home given the ongoing health crisis. Feel free to leave messages or send emails and they will be returned. Our campus is closed until further notice and this includes both gyms, weightrooms or other large gathering spaces.

Once again, we thank you for your support and will continue to communicate as much as possible.

Ned Dale
Superintendent

post_text:
Good afternoon.

I am writing to let you know that we distributed almost 70 breakfast and lunch meals today and we are ready for tomorrow. All Elba students age 3-18 may get the meals for free. If you need meals delivered, we will deliver. Please call 585-757-9967 Ext 1010. We have updated the front page of our website to provide additional learning resources for everyone to see and access. I anticipate that teachers will be calling you to see what we can do to help you with food, as well as to assess the need for additional learning materials and connectivity as we want to support our students during this closure. We are trying to make the best decisions possible and not overwhelm anyone during this health crisis.

Thank you for your support.

Ned Dale

Superintendent

post_text:
Genesee County has declared a state of emergency based on the continued coronavirus health crisis. Based on their recommendation, Elba Central School District will be closed until further notice. We will be communicating additional plans and information Monday. We appreciate your support and understanding, as we continue to prioritize student and staff safety. Only 12 month employees will be asked to report to work at their normal start time.

Ned Dale
Superintendent
585-757-9967 Ext 1034

post_text:
Good Afternoon.

It is with an abundance of caution and guidance from the County Health Director that we cancel this year's musical production of Lion King Junior. During our shows, we would anticipate approximately 250 or more in attendance. Specifically, I have the greatest concerns for grandparents and community members that might be more susceptible to the Coronavirus. We are discussing the possibility of having the cast and crew perform at this year's May concert as a showcase, pending clarification from our licensing agent. Please know that this decision was not taken lightly and was done in collaboration with the best information that we have at this very time. Tickets purchased can be refunded at district office. Mrs. Williams and Mrs. Hoffert will be in touch next week if you sponsored an advertisement.

Thank you!

Ned Dale
Superintendent

Helping Hands is currently selling bracelets custom-made with our school colors. They're very durable, waterproof, and the size is adjustable, so they're able to fit all wrist sizes.
We custom-ordered the bracelets from a company called Pura Vida which employs people living in poverty throughout the world. Not only will our sales benefit our own Elba families in their times of need, but we'll be helping artisans across the globe as well!
If you'd like to purchase one, the selling price is $5 each. Please contact Maria Casper at mcasper@elbacsd.org.

Thank you so much for your continued support of Helping Hands!

Elba Central School is seeking a Varsity Softball Coach.
START DATE: March 9, 2020
Candidate must be available weekdays from approximately 3pm to 7pm. Weekend availability may also be required for certain weeks. Excellent organization and communications skills are required. NY State coaching certification and previous playing and/or coaching experience are preferred, but not required. Coaching inquiries should be directed to Karen Cusmano, Elba Athletic Director at kcusmano@elbacsd.org. Please send letter of interest, resume, ECS application and three (3) professional references.
Deadline: November 15, 2019
